================================================================================
                    CYBERSECURITY AWARENESS CHATBOT
                            PROG6221 - PART 1
================================================================================

PROJECT OVERVIEW
================================================================================
This is a C# console application that functions as a Cybersecurity Awareness
Chatbot. The bot educates users about online safety including password security,
phishing scams, and safe browsing practices.

FEATURES IMPLEMENTED
================================================================================
1. Voice Greeting        - Plays a WAV audio file when the application starts
2. ASCII Art Logo        - Displays a cybersecurity-themed logo at launch
3. Personalized Greeting - Asks for user's name and uses it in responses
4. Response System       - Answers questions about cybersecurity topics
5. Input Validation      - Handles empty or unrecognized inputs gracefully
6. Enhanced Console UI   - Colored text, borders, and typing effect
7. Modular Code Structure- Code organized into separate class files

FILE STRUCTURE
================================================================================
CyberSecurityChatbot/
├── Program.cs           - Main entry point and conversation loop
├── AudioService.cs      - Handles voice greeting playback
├── ChatbotUI.cs         - Console UI methods (ASCII art, colors, typing)
├── ChatbotLogic.cs      - Response logic and cybersecurity advice
├── greeting.wav         - Voice greeting audio file
└── README.txt           - This file

CLASS DESCRIPTIONS
================================================================================
Program.cs
----------
- Contains the Main() method
- Manages the conversation loop
- Calls methods from other classes

AudioService.cs
---------------
- Plays the welcome audio greeting
- Uses System.Media.SoundPlayer
- Handles file not found errors gracefully

ChatbotUI.cs
------------
- DisplayAsciiArt()    - Shows the cybersecurity logo
- GetUserName()        - Asks for and returns user's name
- ShowWelcomeMessage() - Displays welcome message with borders
- TypeWriterEffect()   - Creates typing animation effect
- ShowGoodbyeMessage() - Displays exit message

ChatbotLogic.cs
---------------
- GetResponse()        - Main method that processes user input
- GetPasswordAdvice()  - Returns password safety tips
- GetPhishingAdvice()  - Returns phishing awareness tips
- GetSafeBrowsingAdvice() - Returns safe browsing tips

HOW TO RUN THE APPLICATION
================================================================================
1. Open the solution in Visual Studio
2. Press F5 to build and run
3. If a greeting.wav file is present, it will play
4. Enter your name when prompted
5. Type questions about cybersecurity
6. Type 'exit' or 'quit' to end the conversation

EXAMPLE CONVERSATION
================================================================================
[Bot] May I have your name? Thabo

[Bot] Welcome, THABO!

[Bot] I'm your Cybersecurity Awareness Assistant!
      I can help you learn about:
      - Password Safety
      - Phishing Scams
      - Safe Browsing

You: What is phishing?
[Bot] 🎣 PHISHING AWARENESS:
      - Never click links in unexpected emails
      - Check sender's email address carefully
      - Hover over links to see the real URL
      - Legitimate companies won't ask for passwords via email

You: exit
[Bot] Goodbye, Thabo! Stay safe online!

SUPPORTED QUESTIONS
================================================================================
Category              | Example Questions
----------------------|--------------------------------------------------
General Greetings     | "How are you?"
Purpose               | "What's your purpose?" "What can you do?"
Topics                | "What can I ask about?"
Password Safety       | "Tell me about passwords" "Password tips"
Phishing              | "What is phishing?" "How to spot a scam?"
Safe Browsing         | "Safe browsing tips" "How to stay safe online?"

RESPONSE CONTENT
================================================================================
Password Safety Tips:
- Use passwords at least 12 characters long
- Include uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols
- Don't reuse passwords across multiple accounts
- Use a password manager (Bitwarden, LastPass)
- Never share your password with anyone

Phishing Awareness Tips:
- Never click suspicious links in emails or SMS
- Check sender email addresses carefully
- Hover over links to see the real URL before clicking
- Legitimate companies won't ask for passwords via email
- If it seems urgent or too good to be true, it's probably a scam

Safe Browsing Tips:
- Look for 'https://' and the padlock icon
- Avoid downloading files from untrusted websites
- Keep browser and antivirus software updated
- Use an ad-blocker to avoid malicious ads
- Verify file extensions before opening downloads

TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================
- Operating System: Windows (for audio playback)
- IDE: Visual Studio 2022 or later
- .NET Version: .NET 6.0 or later
- Audio: System.Media.SoundPlayer (requires Windows)

TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================
Issue                          | Solution
-------------------------------|------------------------------------------------
Audio not playing              | Ensure greeting.wav is in bin/Debug/net6.0/
SoundPlayer error              | Add "using System.Media;" to AudioService.cs
Build errors                   | Check class names match between all files
Typing effect not working      | Verify Thread.Sleep() is called correctly

KNOWN ISSUES
================================================================================
- Audio only works on Windows operating systems
- WAV file must be in PCM format for SoundPlayer to work
- Console window size may need adjustment for ASCII art display

